Description: The openeddy package is a software infrastructure for eddy 
    covariance data post-processing. It provides tools for handling data with 
    attached metadata, setting up quality control scheme and summarizing and 
    plotting the results. It is aligned with REddyProc package that provides 
    methods for uStar-filtering, gap-filling, and flux-partitioning. Thus the 
    combined use of openeddy and REddyProc allows to run the whole eddy 
    covariance post-processing chain. Learn more at 
    <https://github.com/lsigut/EC_workflow>.
